50|$|At the 8th <b>Earthwatch</b> {{meeting in}} mid-October 2004 {{it was agreed}} to improve {{collaboration}} between UN agencies. The UN Environment Management Group (EMG) {{had been set up}} to coordinate UN agencies in area related to the environment and human settlements, playing a valuable role in setting policy. It was agreed that <b>Earthwatch</b> and the EMG were complementary and could benefit from sharing results. It was also agreed to consider ways in which <b>Earthwatch</b> could better communicate information.|$|E
